"36:76:5" : {s: 36, a: 76, w: 5, r: "علم", t: "نَعْلَمُ", l: "عَلِمَ", lc: 382, tl: "naʿlamu", lb: "(সে) জানে",e: "[We] know", b: "আমরা (যদি) দেখি/ জানি", i: "Kami mengetahui", f: 5, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows."},
